      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean, i get that they are stereotypes, but for a realistic noir setting, wouldn't the detective lean into those assumptions more heavily? like, if he's walking into a neighborhood like the East Ward, what kind of specific traits or \"red flags\" would he be looking for in people he passes on the street to see if they're connected to the crime? just trying to make the character feel more authentic to that gritty style.",
